  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Ambasciatori is luxurious and modern with a fab location beside Riccione's lovely beachfront promenade. You'll find yourself in a prime spot for spending relaxing days on the sandy beach or exploring the Viale Ceccarini - the heart of the shopping and entertainment district. A 15-minute stroll to the train station means you can easily go further afield too - Bologna is just under an hour away by train.</p>
<p>There’s plenty of opportunity to relax here. Enjoy a swim in the large 50 square metre outdoor pool, which is heated to 28°C or grab a lounger on the wooden decking and soak up the sun. Head across the road to the wide sandy beach if you’d rather have sea views while you sunbathe. The hotel’s got loungers and parasols here that are free for you to use. The highlight of the hotel has to be the new wellness centre. There’s a relaxing hydro massage, sauna and Turkish bath (payable locally).</p>
<p>In the evening we recommend taking a stroll along the promenade which has lots of bars, restaurants and gelaterias. There’s lots of places to choose from for dinner in the town but we can the hotel’s Le Bistrot Restaurant. It’s got great views over the Adriatic Sea and specializes in the traditional cuisine of the Romagna region, created with care by the chef with fresh seasonal produce.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 25 mins by private car from Bologna airport.</p>]]></description>
